                                    <i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> All students who expect to graduate from the Institute by the end of the academic year and are seeking employment may register for campus placements with this office. Placement Registration is for ONE ACADEMIC YEAR ONLY. However, for Long-term internships the registration is valid for 1~2 years. Without registration your candidature for placements/internship is not valid.
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="tab-pane fade" id="pills-pl-cop" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="pills-pl-cop-tab">
                                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> <b>Direct Placement Category:</b> If a student is placed in any company (irrespective of slabs, here slabs are defined w.r.t to the package per annum that a company offers), he/she shall not be allowed for appearing in the other drives both internships & Placements (on-campus & off-campus) hosted by CDPC/departments Concerned. Un-authorized selections (through on-campus/off-campus) will not be entertained during their graduation in the University.</li>
                                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> <b>Long-term Internships with immediate Pre-Placement offer (PPO) category:</b> If a student is placed in any company (irrespective of slabs) as a long-term internee with PPO, he/she shall not be allowed for appearing in the other drives both internships & Placements (on-campus & off-campus) hosted by CDPC/departments Concerned. Un-authorized selections (through on-campus/off-campus) will not be entertained during their graduation in the University.</li>
                                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> <b>Long-term Internships without Pre-Placement offer (PPO) category:</b> If a student is placed in any company (irrespective of slabs) as a long-term intern without PPO falls in the following category:
                                        <br>
                                        <b>a) PPO is promised within a this stipulated time (mostly 3~6 months)</b><br>
                                        The student shall not be allowed for appearing in the other drives both internships & Placements (on-campus & off-campus) hosted by CDPC/departments Concernced for first 3 months (with affective from internship joining date). If PPO is not released in the stipulated time, these category students are allowed for appearing for the drives both internships & Placements (on-campus & off-campus) hosted by CDPC/departments Concernced till they get placed/long-term internship with PPO. Un-authorized selections (through on-campus/off-campus) will not be entertained during their graduation in the University. In addition to this , concerned company has to state the reason (in writing) for not offering the PPO within the stipulated due. There are few instances where company may request for PPO after 1 year but this case usually not recommended for the benefit of the students.<br>
                                        <b>b) PPO is not promised at the time of long-term internship recruitment</b><br>
                                        Usually such internships will be handled separately with due consultation by the concerned departments (particularly HOD & DPN).
                                    </li>
