                                    <i class="fa fa-hand-o-right"></i><b>Student must read the terms and conditions carefully before registering for the company</b>
                                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i>There are as many as instances where students are: registering for the company but not appearing, appearing but not participating in further selection process, get selected in participating selection process but withdrawing the offer. In these cases, the following are the measures for smooth completion of the drive & avoiding the loss of opportunities to other students.</li>
                                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> <b>Registered for the drive but not participated without any valid reason:</b> If this verified and approved by CDPC & Department (HOD& DPN), then student will not be allowed for the very next drive. Still after the first disciplinary action student repeats the same then he/she will not be allowed for drives for entire semester. After this disciplinary action, students did same then he/she will not be allowed for rest of the drives. Here “Valid reason” could be medical grounds, attending the departmental events or any other event authorized by DPN/HOD.</li>
                                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> <b>Appeared for one of the selection process but not participated in further selection process without any valid reason:</b> If this verified and approved by CDPC & Department (HOD& DPN), then student will not be allowed for the very next 2 drives. Still after the first disciplinary action student repeats the same then he/she will not be allowed for drives for entire semester. After this disciplinary action, students did same then he/she will not be allowed for rest of the drives. Here "Valid reason" Could be medical grounds, attending the departmental events or any other event authorized by DPN/HOD.</li>
                                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> <b>Get selected in participating selection process but withdrawing the offer:</b> This case will be seriously viewed and the student will not be allowed for further drives both internships & Placements (on-campus & off-campus) hosted by CDPC/departments.</li>
                                    <li><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i> <b>If the student attended for 1 or more Drive processes conducted by CDPC and If he/she got an offer from one company they should stick to that offer on one student one offer.</b></li>
